member.name: T:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment
member.summary: Defines horizontal alignment of text

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.General
member.summary: The horizontal alignment is general-aligned. Text data is left-aligned. Numbers, dates, and times are right- aligned. Boolean types are centered. Changing the alignment does not change the type of data.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.Left
member.summary: The horizontal alignment is left-aligned, even in Right-to-Left mode. Aligns contents at the left edge of the cell. If an indent amount is specified, the contents of the cell is indented from the left by the specified number of character spaces. The character spaces are based on the default font and font size for the workbook.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.Center
member.summary: The horizontal alignment is centered, meaning the text is centered across the cell.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.Right
member.summary: The horizontal alignment is right-aligned, meaning that cell contents are aligned at the right edge of the cell, even in Right-to-Left mode.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.Fill
member.summary: Indicates that the value of the cell should be filled across the entire width of the cell. If blank cells to the right also have the fill alignment, they are also filled with the value, using a convention similar to centerContinuous.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.Justify
member.summary: The horizontal alignment is justified (flush left and right). For each line of text, aligns each line of the wrapped text in a cell to the right and left (except the last line). If no single line of text wraps in the cell, then the text is not justified.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.CenterContinuous
member.summary: The horizontal alignment is centered across multiple cells. The information about how many cells to span is expressed in the Sheet Part, in the row of the cell in question. For each cell that is spanned in the alignment, a cell element needs to be written out, with the same style Id which references the centerContinuous alignment.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.HorizontalAlignment.Distributed
member.summary: I/ndicates that each 'word' in each line of text inside the cell is evenly distributed across the width of the cell, with flush right and left margins.

member.name: T:Codaxy.Xlio.VerticalAlignment
member.summary: Defines vertical alignment of text inside a cell.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.VerticalAlignment.Top
member.summary: The vertical alignment is aligned-to-top.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.VerticalAlignment.Center
member.summary: The vertical alignment is centered across the height of the cell.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.VerticalAlignment.Bottom
member.summary: The vertical alignment is aligned-to-bottom.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.VerticalAlignment.Justify
member.summary: When text direction is horizontal: the vertical alignment of lines of text is distributed vertically, where each line of text inside the cell is evenly distributed across the height of the cell, with flush top and bottom margins.

member.name: F:Codaxy.Xlio.VerticalAlignment.Distributed
member.summary: When text direction is horizontal: the vertical alignment of lines of text is distributed vertically, where each line of text inside the cell is evenly distributed across the height of the cell, with flush top and bottom margins.
